No. 2343. Miller v. Monk.

November Term, 1888.

February 6, 1889. W. A. Williams, for appellant. T. 0. Monk, contra.

Opinion by

Mr. Chiee Justice Simpson,

Judgment by a trial justice on an open account for goods furnished, afiSrmed by the Circuit Court (Aldrich, J.), was appealed to this court on exceptions which alleged error only in the findings of fact below. Held, that this court was without jurisdiction.
